captions.text: I went hiking with my, Clayton.
- No, it's actually, well, it's him.

The guy with the shirt
that's too small for him?

- I think it's just more
that his muscles are too big.
- Yeah, I think they are too big.

He can't scratch his own back,
it's kind of stupid, right?

- (laughs) You're right,
I'm gonna go help him.

- [Ashly] What are you doing?
- [Clayton] Bring it in.
- So there I was, vomit frozen in my beard

from the altitude sickness,
and here comes mama polar bear,
looks at me, nods, and just walks on by.

- This one time at the zoo,
I was throwing up a lot,

because all I had to eat
that day was ice cream.

It was in front of a
polar bear exhibit, so...

- Aren't they the best?
- Yeah, yeah.

- [Girls] Yeah, so cute.
- [Clayton] Yeah, I know.
- Hey, uh, who's that new guy?

- [Blue-Haired Girl]
Well, you know, that's a,

- He also took a big dump
in the bathroom, so...

- [Clayton] This is too easy
- [Ashly] Oh my god, come on.

- [Clayton] You can't guard.
- [Ashly] It's not my fault

- Okay, where am I?
- What am I supposed-
- This is how you play basketball, ugh!

- Oh my god.
- Are you okay?
